{"questionId":"9072734","questionHtml":"<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">A student measures the radius <em>R</em> of a circular plate to determine its area. The absolute uncertainty in <em>R</em> is Δ<em>R</em>.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">What is the <strong>fractional</strong> uncertainty in the area of the plate?</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">A.&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{{2\\Delta R}}{R}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n      <mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Δ</mi>\n      <mi>R</mi>\n    </mrow>\n    <mi>R</mi>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span></span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">B.&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{\\left( {\\frac{{\\Delta R}}{R}} \\right)^2}\">\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mrow>\n        <mo>(</mo>\n        <mrow>\n          <mfrac>\n            <mrow>\n              <mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Δ</mi>\n              <mi>R</mi>\n            </mrow>\n            <mi>R</mi>\n          </mfrac>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo>)</mo>\n      </mrow>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span></span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">C.&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{{2\\pi \\Delta R}}{R}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n      <mi>π</mi>\n      <mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Δ</mi>\n      <mi>R</mi>\n    </mrow>\n    <mi>R</mi>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span></span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">D.&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\pi {\\left( {\\frac{{\\Delta R}}{R}} \\right)^2}\">\n  <mi>π</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mrow>\n        <mo>(</mo>\n        <mrow>\n          <mfrac>\n            <mrow>\n              <mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Δ</mi>\n              <mi>R</mi>\n            </mrow>\n            <mi>R</mi>\n          </mfrac>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo>)</mo>\n      </mrow>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span></span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>A</p>","meta":{"questionId":"9072734","referenceCode":"19M.1.SL.TZ2.1","subjectId":"46-dp-physics-last-assessment-2024","title":"A student measures the radius R of a circular plate to determine its area. The absolute uncertainty in R is ΔR. What is the fractional uncertainty in the area of the plate? A. 2 Δ ","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"1","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Core","Core","Topic 1: Measurements and uncertainties","1.2 – Uncertainties and errors","Core","Topic 1: Measurements and uncertainties"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}